{{cooknav}}

Recipes from [[Cookbook:Cuisine of Cuba|Cuba]].
[[Category:North American recipes]]

{{unit}}

A '''pinch''' is a very informal unit, equal to the amount of powder that can comfortably be held between the thumb and forefinger.  It is roughly equal to 1/8 [[Cookbook:Teaspoon|teaspoon]].

If this were accurate, which it's not, the metric equivalent would be 0.625 [[Cookbook:mL|mL]]. Call it 1/2 mL or 2/3 mL if you like.

